-- Credit Suisse's Bourgeois to Join Atlantic-Pacific as CEO
-- B y   S a b r i n a   W i l l m e r
-- 2012-07-10T04:01:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-10/credit-suisse-s-bourgeois-to-join-atlantic-pacific-as-ceo.html
Mark Bourgeois, head of the Americas
at  Credit Suisse Group AG’s (CS)  asset management group, has left to
become chief executive officer and president of placement agent
and advisory firm Atlantic-Pacific Capital, according to a
statement from New York-based Atlantic-Pacific.  Alastair Cairns will replace Bourgeois as head of Americas
for the Swiss bank’s money management group and Charles Shaffer
is taking over Bourgeois’s role as head of distribution, said
Suzanne Fleming, a spokeswoman for Credit Suisse Asset
Management.  While at Credit Suisse, Bourgeois oversaw fund investments
made by the bank in the Americas, and headed distribution for
the asset management division. Atlantic-Pacific Capital helps
alternative asset managers raise money.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sabrina Willmer in  New York  at 
